[[美国国家航空航天局|美国国家航空航天局]][[戈达德太空研究所|戈达德太空研究所]]和其他机构曾推测，20亿年前，[[金星|金星]]上可能曾有过一座浅海<ref>{{cite journal |author=Hashimoto, G. L. |author2=Roos-Serote, M. |author3=Sugita, S. |author4=Gilmore, M. S. |author5=Kamp, L. W. |author6=Carlson, R. W. |author7=Baines, K. H. |title=Felsic highland crust on Venus suggested by Galileo Near-Infrared Mapping Spectrometer data |journal=[[Journal_of_Geophysical_Research:_Planets|Journal of Geophysical Research: Planets]] |date=2008 |volume=113 |issue=E9 |doi=10.1029/2008JE003134 |pages=E00B24 |bibcode=2008JGRE..113.0B24H}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=David Shiga |url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/dn12769-did-venuss-ancient-oceans-incubate-life.html#.UiwMq8ZMvlU |title=Did Venus's ancient oceans incubate life? |work=New Scientist |date=10 October 2007}}</ref><ref name="WV2016">{{cite journal|title=Was Venus the First Habitable World of our Solar System?|author=Michael J. Way|display-authors=etal|journal=[[Geophysical_Research_Letters|Geophysical Research Letters]]|date=26 August 2016|doi=10.1002/2016GL069790|pmid=28408771|pmc=5385710|volume=43|issue = 16|pages=8376–8383|arxiv = 1608.00706 |bibcode = 2016GeoRL..43.8376W }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://climate.nasa.gov/news/2475/nasa-climate-modeling-suggests-venus-may-have-been-habitable/|title=NASA climate modeling suggests Venus may have been habitable|author=Michael Cabbage and Leslie McCarthy|work=[[NASA|NASA]]|date=11 August 2016|accessdate=19 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/hellish-venus-might-have-been-habitable-for-billions-of-years/|title=Hellish Venus Might Have Been Habitable for Billions of Years|author=Shannon Hall|work=[[Scientific_American|Scientific American]]|date=10 August 2016|accessdate=19 November 2016}}</ref>，其水量与地球上的一样多<ref name="ESAH">{{cite web|url=http://www.esa.int/Our_Activities/Space_Science/Venus_Express/Where_did_Venus_s_water_go|title=Where did Venus's water go?|work=[[European_Space_Agency|European Space Agency]]|date=18 December 2008|accessdate=19 November 2016}}</ref>。根据他们理论模型中所使用的参数，最后的液态水可能在7.15亿年前蒸发殆尽<ref name="WV2016" />。目前，金星上唯一已知的水是[[金星大气层|大气层]]中微量的[[水蒸气|水蒸气]](20[[百万分率|ppm]])<ref name=Basilevsky2003>{{cite journal|last=Basilevsky|first=Alexandr T.|author2=Head, James W.|title=The surface of Venus|journal=Rep. Prog. Phys.|date=2003|volume=66|issue=10|pages=1699–1734|doi=10.1088/0034-4885/66/10/R04 |bibcode = 2003RPPh...66.1699B }}</ref><ref name=Bertaux2007>{{cite journal| last=Bertaux|first=Jean-Loup| title=A warm layer in Venus' cryosphere and high-altitude measurements of HF, HCl, H2O and HDO| journal=Nature| date=2007| volume=450| pages=646–649| doi=10.1038/nature05974| bibcode=2007Natur.450..646B| pmid=18046397|issue=7170| author2=Vandaele, Ann-Carine| last3=Korablev|first3=Oleg|last4=Villard|first4=E.|last5=Fedorova|first5=A.|last6=Fussen|first6=D.|last7=Quémerais|first7=E.|last8=Belyaev|first8=D.|last9=Mahieux|first9=A. |s2cid=4421875| display-authors=8 }}</ref>。[[氢|氢]]是水的一种成分，[[欧洲空间局|欧空局]][[金星特快车|金星特快车]]航天器探测到，如今仍在向太空流失<ref name="ESAH"/>。

